<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN303-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. erumai veḷiyaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN303">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>nilampiṟak kiṭuvatu pōṟkuḷampu kaṭaiyūu</l>
<l>vuḷḷa moḻikkuṅ koṭpiṉ māṉmē</l>
<l>leḷḷunarc cekukkuṅ kāḷai kūrtta</l>
<l>ventiṟa leḵka neñcuvaṭu viḷaippa</l>
<l>vāṭṭik kāṇiya varumē nerunai</l>
<l>yuraicāl ciṟappiṉ vēntar muṉṉark</l>
<l>karaiporu munnīrt tiraiyiṟ pōḻntavar</l>
<l>kayantalai maṭappiṭi pulampa</l>
<l>vilaṅkumarup piyāṉai yeṟinta veṟkē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The young man who destroys those who deride [him], (3a-c)</l>
<l>upon a restless horse that finishes off the mind (2)</l>
<l>by pressing down [its] hooves as if putting behind the ground, (1)</l>
<l>with [his] sharp cruel powerful blade he made [them] fade </l>
<l>when [their] hearts were exhausted by [their] injuries [and] comes in order to see (4-5c)</l>
<l>me who yesterday had attacked an elephant with shining tusks (5d+9)</l>
<l>so that [its] soft-headed youthful elephant cow would be lonely, (8)</l>
<l>[the elephant] of the kings with praise-worthy excellence (6a-c)</l>
<l>who had previously cut into [our front numerous] like the waves of the sea that beats against the shore. (6d-7)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
